element.name: Dublin Can Be Heaven by Kili or bust, Multi-cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit The Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

long-description.p:
"Dublin can be Heaven, with coffee at eleven,
and a stroll in Stephen's Green".......
Lovely centre city park for a visitor and the stages of this cache will show you very quickly around.
In spring and summer time it is open for lengthy periods and the plant life and floral displays can be pretty special.
N.B Any early morning visit would be a good idea!!! And preferably on a weekday as the park can be quite crowded at weekends
The coords bring you to an information board where you will quickly find the locations of the 3 clues to the coords for the cache. Very close to the cache is another information board with all the history of "The Green" you may wish to know.
1. How many figures (excluding the dog) are displayed behind the Wolfe Tone Memorial? Answer goes where the question mark is. The rest of the missing coords are in the next 2 questions.
N 53 20.?-- W 006 15.---
2. On the back of James Joyce's collar M. Fitzgibbon's year is displayed. Divide it by 2 then subtract 391 and fill in the 3 question marks below.
N 53 20.--- W 006 15.???
3. Robert Emmet died in 18?3. This figure is used twice in the remaining missing coords.
N 53 20.-?? W 006 15---
Now you have the coords for the cache which is quite small so try not to bring anything chunky to place in it. It is in a small flat tupperware box in a ziploc bag. Spoiler picture included. The green liner is now gone so you are looking for a see through tupperware box with a green lid. This is to help anyone who finds the tree cover interfering with the coords.

element.encoded-hints: 36 paces from fountain through left side of gazebo to wooden sleepers behind. Piece of wood screwed on to hold it in.

Nice walk around the park. Together with 4-voeters we made a mistake and discovered that the coords were not correct. With the help of the discription and the hints we were able to locate the cache anyway. It was extremely busy at this bank holliday. There was a mini marathon for women going on and that brought a lot of people to this area. Everyone, including us, had a lot of fun. Logged at 13:50 T4TC
